[normal]38.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The whole of the female pathway needs to be considered when examining sports policy. 
[normal]Increasing the physical literacy at an early age and ensurin
[normal]g girls receive quality coaching focused to their needs at schools will hugely help to ensure that girls enjoy sport and have the opportunity to play if they want to. 
[normal]The current school clubs links programmes are vital to prevent drop off after school and 
[normal]support should continue for these programmes, perhaps with additional funding for girls’ initiatives. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]39.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]For grassroots football, ensuring that facilities are available and of suitable standard will be a challenge in the years to come as the ability to inve
[normal]st in and maintain current facilities will come under further pressure. Meanwhile, while elite football is growing stronger, government can play a key role in encouraging media coverage which is so vital for attracting sponsorship to reinvest into the game
[normal]. 
