[normal]Before 1993 the Women’s Football Association (WFA) was responsible for the women’s game. The WFA was as an independent body in 1969 and was not part of The FA. 
[normal]It focussed on the then fledgling international competitions and even took an England side to th
[normal]e finals of the European Championship in 1984. However, they were unable to develop the game at grassroots level due to limited funding.
